Global Funds Buy Net 15.5 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-03-15T03:19:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/global-funds-buy-net-15-5-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 15.5
billion rupees ($344 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1.1 percent to 915.4 billion rupees, or 33
percent of gross market position, according to the exchangeâ€™s
website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on
Sept. 21.  Foreign investors bought a net 4.14 billion rupees of
shares in the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary
data given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
